    "GTEx: The Genotype-Tissue Expression (GTEx) project (the images originated from tissues processed using alternative fixatives to formalin; only slides showing preserved glandular morphology were considered for the evaluation and included images with prostatitis).",
    "The 11th test condition is provided in the supplementary results section.",
    "The results are provided in more detail in the supplementary results section.",
    "Gleason pattern is also considered a secondary Gleason pattern, and the second most common Gleason pattern is considered a tertiary Gleason pattern.",
    "Given that our previous study on an independent cohort with radical prostatectomy specimens revealed a pathologist-related underestimation of the tumor area (underestimation bias) by approximately half (50%) of the original tumor percentage 4, we corrected this threshold to 10%."
  ],
